lib.frc1747.motion_profile.generator._2d

Class QuinticBezier

  • java.lang.Object
    • lib.frc1747.motion_profile.generator._2d.QuinticBezier

  • public class QuinticBezier
extends java.lang.Object
    A quintic bezier class used for generating splines with C2 continuity. Concepts taken from the article "Planning Motion Trajectories for Mobile Robots Using Splines" by Christoph Sprunk
    Author:
    Tiger Huang

      • uniformTimePositionSample

        public double[] uniformTimePositionSample(int samples)
        Returns the specified number of position samples from this curve.
        Parameters:
        samples - The number of segments to sample
        Returns:

        The points are arranged as [x0, y0, x1, y1, ...]

      • uniformTimeArcLengthSample

        public double[][] uniformTimeArcLengthSample(int samples)
        Returns an array containing corresponding times and arc positions.
        Parameters:
        samples - The number of segments to sample
        Returns:
        An array associating times and arc positions
        The format is [t0, s0; t1, s1; ...]

      • uniformLengthSegmentData

        public double[][] uniformLengthSegmentData(int timeSampleCount,
                                           double sampleLength)
        Flattens the 2D profile into a 1D profile that is parameterized for arc length.
        Parameters:
        timeSampleCount - The number of equal time segments to initially estimate
        sampleLength - The target arc length of the output segments
        Returns:
        A flattened profile in the form delta arc length and delta theta.
        The format is [ds0, dtheta0; ds1, dtheta1; ...]
